"can be used to obtain the sample size automatically: 1. Select the function STATCALC. 2. Select the option ''sample size.'' 3. Specify:\n. the size of the population (e.g. 5,000)\nthe estimated frequency of the condition sought (e.g. 15%)\nthe lower or higher limit (e.g. 10%) 4. Press F4 to obtain the result (e.g. 189). \n# Tools for the Statistical Analysis of Sample Data\n\n# Basic Principles\nAs explained above, for a given population the means obtained from several samples of the same size will produce an average which will deviate more or less from the true mean, as calculated from the entire population."